"text","value":"In "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"my first article"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"./i-cannot-edit-that"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" I barely scratched the surface of\nwhat is missing to encourage collaboration on public available data. In this\narticle I‚Äôd like to share my view of what is missing."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I have a publicized a list of technology user groups from my area at\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"usergroups.rheinmainrocks.de"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://usergroups.rheinmainrocks.de/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". The list\nis driven by a collection of XML files describing each group. The XML files are\nhosted in a "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"GIT repository at GitHub"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/tacker/ugrm-data","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":".\nThey can be edited by everybody."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#everybody-can-edit-public-on-github-already-everybody","ariaLabel":"everybody can edit public on github already everybody permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Everybody can edit public on GitHub already. "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Everybody?"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"everybody-can-edit-public-on-github-already-everybody","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Well, at least if he is accustomed to the git pull request workflow, the file\nformat in place, can speak english (as this is GitHubs only interface language),\nhas an account on github.com."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"If I want every member of my audience to enhance my collection of data about\nusergroups‚ÄîGitHub pull requests on XML files would not be the choice. I picked\nit because it is easy to manage. From a contributors point of view another\napproach would be much more feasable: fill in some kind of form and be done with\nit."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#look-ma-no-login","ariaLabel":"look ma no login permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Look Ma! No login!"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"look-ma-no-login","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Yes, I am talking about anonymous submissions. I can decide on the submitted\ndata if it fits into my context. Author information is nice to have but not\nrequired."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I really don‚Äôt care who is submitting information‚Äî"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"the information is what\nmatters"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"To encourage contributions to data the process must be as easy as ordering\nsomething from amazon: straight forward and self explanatory. But the tools we\nhave at the moment are fare from that. In my industry we call the content\nmanagement systems. And the emphasis is on management and system. Those are\nbeasts in terms of functionality and versatility which is achieved by throwing\nmassive collections of buttons and input elements at the users without any\nexplanation. For every CMS you need not only the vendors handbook, but an\ninstruction on how to use the system for the specific site it was adapted for."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#admin-areas-must-vanish","ariaLabel":"admin areas must vanish permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Admin areas must vanish!"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"admin-areas-must-vanish","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Admin areas‚Äîthe thing behind the username and password fields‚Äîare designed for\nusers to edit content. If the content for every website can easily be classified\ninto a few‚Äîtext, lists, links, images‚Äîwhy must there be a custom way to edit\nthese in every CMS?"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"It is these admin areas which function as a blocker for contributions."}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"If we could establish an easy to use and standardized way to orchestrate the\nediting, review and approval of content on the web we could focus on publishing\ncontent instead of setting up systems for its management."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#protocols-are-for-machines","ariaLabel":"protocols are for machines permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Protocols are for machines"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"protocols-are-for-machines","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"There is a\nprotocol‚Äî"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"AtomPup"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://bitworking.org/projects/atom/rfc5023.html","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"‚Äîwhich\nenables the collaboration on arbitrary data in a system neutral way. This is\nachieved by defining a set of actions‚Äîknown as the CRUD operations‚Äîand\nstrategies to handle conflicts. It is a robust and universally approach but it\nlacks an important aspect: it does not care about the data to be edited. For the\nscope of the protocol this is the right approach. There is no need to care about\nthe data‚ÄîAtomPub is just a messenger. The implementation of the content editing\nis left to the user and he is forced to acquire the suitable tools."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","pr